What is the running time of the following code snippet in Big-Oh notation?

```cpp
int CALC(int n)
{
    if (n < 10)
        return 0;
    else
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i += 2)
        {
            cout << i;
        }
    return n;
}

int main()
{
    int n; // assume n is defined elsewhere
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
        int res = CALC(i);
    return 0;
}
```
